### ADDENDUM 1: Memory-Safe Grouped Ingestion Protocol



For large CSV files that may cause memory issues, load in chunks and concatenate:



```python

def load_compact_chunked(filepath, chunksize=10000):

    chunks = []

    for chunk in pd.read_csv(filepath, chunksize=chunksize):

        chunk.columns = chunk.columns.str.replace(r'\\', '', regex=True)

        chunk = chunk.drop_duplicates(

            subset=['Player','Date','Venue','Opposition','Category','Main','Minutes'])

        chunks.append(chunk)

    df = pd.concat(chunks, ignore_index=True)

    df = df.drop_duplicates(

        subset=['Player','Date','Venue','Opposition','Category','Main','Minutes'])

    print(f"[CHUNKED LOAD] Total rows after dedup: {len(df)}")

    return df

```



